messages.message: Hey folks I know that for Lists - we can only have 10 attributes, is there a reason for this limit? At Rippling we have case where we want to make 15+ attributes.

@Vishnu found that accuracy was lower with higher number of attributes

what is the desired number of attributes for Rippling?
it's not a cost thing - they just need this table. We could almost even have a transformation capability with unique identifiers

could we create the 15 attributes as separate fields? this generally results in higher accuracy as well

is there a reason that these attributes need to be in a single field?
Yes - they will be used as unique entries to route specific workflows. Therefore, the data needs to be coupled across the row
Which is why it needs to be a table
can you provide a sample doc and describe the data that needs to be extracted?

No I canâ€™t - it is a customer account & their PII data. The documents are a sheet that has a table from which we need to pull all the data from, and need to append a secondary field. We have been able to do so, however the limited number of fields leads us to need to do a list of objects extraction twice with a unique identifier
@Serena there is a world with non-extracted field where we can pull these fields into one and send it off. However, we want to get a resolution for today also
